Published Friday, 2025-11-21, including PRs merged Friday, 2025-11-14 through Thursday, 2025-11-20.
íŸ@65e6edbd65152c2e6d445764663e3b4e46b4e4207a2b8639f47b6d5bdfc762f2⁄¢Title: title: 'This week in Nushell #326'
Path: Nushell
Content:
@fdncred:
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17045] added rfind ability to the find command (#17045)
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17023] updated to latest reedline (#17023)
@app/dependabot:
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17043] bumped crate-ci/typos from 1.39.0 to 1.39.2 (#17043)
@Dorumin:
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17039] added --dry to mktemp (#17039)
@KaiSforza:
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17037] added all 
``LabeledError``
 structure parts to 
``error make``
 (#17037)
@Jan9103:
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17036] fixed into_sqlite by passing a span along (#17036)
@mrdgo:
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17035] fixed a typo (#17035)
@cptpiepmatz:
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17030] improved DNS-related errors (#17030)
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17022] used 
``rustc``
 as external instead of 
``sleep``
 for highlight test (#17022)
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17019] used native cert store on Android for rustls (#17019)
@blindFS:
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17026] included already parsed module names in dotnu completion (#17026)
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17025] fixed wrong span of 
``export def/extern``
 with attributes & snippet completion for attributable commands (#17025)
@WindSoilder:
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17017] added 
``call: DynamicCompletionCall``
 parameter to 
``get_dynamic_completion``
 and allowed returning span (#17017)
@taearls:
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/16999] improved error message when 
``plugin add``
 fails due to missing config directory (#16999)
@Tyarel8:
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/16933] added example on how to delete original columns in 
``group-by``
 (#16933)
